ANNOUNCEMENTS (03): PROMED-MAIL SEEKING VIRAL DISEASE MODERATOR
***************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 10 Mar 2014
From: Larry Madoff <lmadoff@promedmail.org>


ProMED-mail, the Program for Monitoring Emerging Diseases of the International Society for Infectious Diseases, is seeking a highly qualified individual to fill a part-time Viral Diseases Moderator position. The individual will join an international team of over 40 global health specialists located in 25 countries.

Key responsibilities and duties
-------------------------------
Reporting:
1. Using an online dashboard tool, post relevant reports of events of interest in viral diseases with appropriate commentary in a timely manner (less than 24 hours). Reports should include short, knowledgeable, appropriate contextual commentaries with background information.
2. Actively and regularly search the Internet -- including the web, local media, disease outbreak sources of information (such as HealthMap), social media platforms, and relevant blogs -- for reports of outbreaks of emerging infectious diseases.
3. Find relevant regional and national email lists and websites of universities and professional societies, to which you can solicit subscriptions and contributions of reports to ProMED.
4. Assist in recruitment of new subscribers and outreach at regional, national, and international professional conferences and meetings.
5. Respond to requests from subscribers

Inter- and Intra- staff:
6. Assist in training of new staff.
7. Attend periodic meetings (annual or biannual) of ProMED staff.
8. Submit to the ProMED-mail Editor an informal monthly report, and a formal quarterly report of your activities, specifying the number of outbreak items you've found; the number of ProMED messages you moderated; and the number of invitations to join ProMED-mail you forwarded to relevant individuals or lists; plus any other information you believe to be of interest to ProMED-mail.
9. Set a regular schedule with ProMED-mail Editor and notify him/her in advance of any expected absence from moderation duties.
10. Contact Moderators with any questions or suggestions for improving ProMED.

Qualifications
--------------
1. Doctoral-level degree in the human/animal health field, with specialization and expertise in virology and viral diseases required (MD, MBBS, DVM, PhD in microbiology or similar field) with strong interest in emerging infectious diseases. Additional advanced degree in a related field a plus.
2. Ten or more years of experience in human or animal infectious diseases, specifically in diagnosis, treatment, and/or research.
3. A track record of achievement in academic, governmental, or nongovernmental organization commensurate with career stage.
4. Ability and interest in maintaining expertise in infectious diseases through continuing education.
5. Email and Web proficiency and daily access.
6. Familiarity with ProMED archives.
7. Fluency in written and spoken English.

Compensation
------------
- A modest annual stipend of USD 5460 will be paid.
- An additional USD 750 is provided as a reimbursement for IT expenses.
- Compensation for travel to required ProMED staff/editorial meetings will also be provided.

Interested individuals should forward a cover letter summarizing interests and qualifications and curriculum vitae to <positions@isid.org>, with the subject line: "Moderator, Viral Diseases". We will accept applications until 24 Mar 2014.

--
Larry Madoff, MD
Editor, ProMED-mail
<lmadoff@promedmail.orgf>

